post: The underlying logic of the DIF (Difference) is that the short-term Exponential Moving Average (EMA) reflects the current price trend, while the long-term EMA reflects earlier price trends. Therefore, if there is a significant gap between these two EMAs, it indicates that the market is trending either upwards or downwards. The MACD Histogram oscillating near the zero line indicates the strength of the trend

post: British consumer price inflation rose for the first time this year in July, but at a slower rate than expected as prices for services, which are closely watched by the Bank of England, rose at a slower pace, official data released on Wednesday showed. Annual consumer price inflation rose to 2.2 per cent two months after the Bank of England's 2 per cent target was maintained, slightly below the median forecast of 2.3 per cent in a Reuters poll of economists, the Office for National Statistics said. The pound fell sharply against the dollar after the data was released, with financial markets expecting a 44 per cent chance of a 25 basis point rate cut by the Bank of England in September, up from 36 per cent before the data was released.

post: " Identifying and understanding the primary and secondary trends is important because it can help make better decisions about when to enter or exit a position. For example, if the primary trend is bullish (upward) but the secondary trend experiences a brief pullback (downward correction), traders can take advantage of the opportunity to purchase the asset at a lower price in anticipation that the primary trend will continue to move upward in the long term. On the other hand, if the primary trend is bearish (downward) but there is a brief upward correction in the secondary trend, the trader can use this opportunity to sell the asset at a higher price, as the primary trend is expected to continue to move downward in the long term"

post: In summary, the MACD indicator is very simple and practical, but it does have some drawbacks. Since moving averages reflect a stock's price changes over a previous period, MACD may not immediately generate signals in response to significant short-term price movements, leading to some lag. Therefore, when using the MACD indicator for signal and trading decisions, it is advisable to combine it with other indicators for a more comprehensive analysis
